I didn't used full-bleeds very often in the old days, but whereever I did, I have to extend it so it goes to the edge of the paper.
Though it's a lot of work, most people probably wont even notice.
Here's an example. Almost unnoticable, but all the edges are expanded, which means they're drawing in from scratch.
I could just expand, but it would both decrease the quality, and people would end up cut off.
because the edges get chopped off. It's called the bleed area.
It's a buffer zone. So blowing up artwork means the edges get cut.
But if you don't, you might end up with white edges.
